&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SSH Server Refused Our Key</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/server-refused-our-key/</link><pubDate>Sat, 28 Mar 2020 17:48:55 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://finisky.github.io/en/server-refused-our-key/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;After I changed the HOME folder to another place, I copied the ssh config folder from old HOME to the new place. Supposedly it should directly work, right? However, when I login the server with my private key, the server said: &amp;ldquo;Server Refused Our Key&amp;rdquo;&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- more --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I spent some time to figure out the problem: new HOME folder access mode issue, it SHOULD NOT have write access for group.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>